listContent.textHtml: The opportunity: Companies struggle with AI adoption because legacy systems and ways of working are so entrenched and people are so resistant to change that wholesale AI reinventon remains nearly impossible within an existing company. So the opportunity - look at industries and build AI first companies from the ground up that will be acquired by the legacy companies as they seek to modernize their operation and acquire improvements in margin. Or, acquire legacy companies and implement the AI first systems.... where in the business model is AI uniquely positioned to win? Where do humans play?
